WEBVTT

00:02:29.414 --> 00:02:30.663
They chanted things like,

00:02:30.687 --> 00:02:32.935
"The flag and the artist,
hang them both high,"

00:02:32.959 --> 00:02:34.483
evoking images of lynching.

00:02:34.507 --> 00:02:36.145
I received numerous death threats,

00:02:36.169 --> 00:02:38.299
and bomb threats
were phoned in to my school.

00:02:38.323 --> 00:02:40.003
It was a very dangerous situation.

00:02:40.401 --> 00:02:42.934
Later, President Bush called
the work "disgraceful,"

00:02:42.958 --> 00:02:44.753
which I viewed as a tremendous honor,

00:02:44.777 --> 00:02:46.302
and Congress outlawed the work.

00:02:46.326 --> 00:02:47.431
(Laughter)

00:02:47.455 --> 00:02:51.472
I became part of a Supreme Court case
when I and others defied that law,

00:02:51.496 --> 00:02:53.681
by burning flags
on the steps of the Capitol.

00:02:54.485 --> 00:02:57.605
That action and the subsequent
legal and political battle

